experience.description:
Model-free tracking utilizing properties of dynamical control systems
Supervisor: Dr. Stas Tiomkin
The aim is to learn intrinsic properties of dynamical control systems from samples without recovering the full dynamical model for efficient tracking. The properties of interest are equivariant and invariant, which we propose to learn from samples by modern methods from deep learning, dynamical control
systems, and estimation.
experience.title: Graduate Research Assistant

experience.description:
1. Twilytics : A Social Perception Analysis of Public Transit Systems using twitter data during COVID-19. I am leading this project, working as a Research assistant under Dr. Egbe-Etu supervision, responsible for entire data engineering and data science pipeline. The project is funded by Mineta Transportation Institute –US Department of Transportation.

2. Investigating the Usability and Effectiveness of Public Transportation Technology in Older Adults during a Public Health Crisis. I am working with Dr. Gaojian Huang to optimize passenger and freight movements to improve mobility of people and goods through development of more accurate data models and advanced application of analytical tools. The project is funded by Mineta Transportation Institute – US Department of Transportation.
